channel.title: [Question] Difference between Delta and PI?
channel.description: I've been working with a blank 317 Delta source for a few weeks now, and it's nice and I've got a pretty good grasp on how to work them. My question is, what's the difference between Delta and Project Insanity? It seems as if it's packaged/bundled differently, and the syntax seems to be a bit different. I was thinking of switching to PI, what's the difference and which would you recommend? I'm not releasing a server, I'm doing 317s purely to better my Java knowledge, so please don't comment saying, "677, 722, 728" shit like that.. Thanks! - The Web Guy

item.title: [Question] Difference between Delta and PI?
item.dc:creator: @enzo42 enzo42
item.description:
@enzo42 wrote:

[quote=“wartek, post:2, topic:461311”]delta: 70% of the source is in client.java
pi: everything is in it’s own file , like the commands are in the command.java, unlike delta.
Imo pi is much easyer to work with then delta…[/quote]

Clean deltas like randqm’s blakes and mine do not have 70% of the content in client.java

PI is for lazy ass people who just leech everything.
